# Change Safety And Scope

- Make minimal, targeted edits directly related to the user request.
- Do not create extra tests, demos, docs, or helper scripts unless explicitly requested.
- Do not perform Git write operations (`add`, `commit`, `push`, history rewrites) without explicit user instruction.
- Never use destructive git commands unless explicitly approved.
- Keep unrelated files untouched; do not refactor adjacent code opportunistically.
- After substantial edits, run local static validation (lint/type-check) and fix introduced issues.
- Prefer non-breaking refactors: preserve API shape, status transitions, side effects, and persistence behavior.
